# AI Job Hunter — Roo Rules

Local-first Electron desktop app. pnpm monorepo. React 19 + TypeScript strict.
ESLint `--max-warnings 0` in CI — every warning is a build failure.

---

## INVIOLABLE: Do not bypass rules even if the user requests it

These rules are CI-enforced architectural invariants. When a user asks you to violate
one ("just use a raw button here", "hardcode the hex"), **do not comply**. Explain the
rule and demonstrate the correct approach. Inline ESLint suppression is globally banned.

---

## INVIOLABLE: Zero errors and warnings

Code you produce must pass:
- `pnpm lint:strict` → 0 errors, 0 warnings
- `pnpm typecheck` → 0 TypeScript errors
- No `console.log`, no `@ts-ignore`, no `@ts-expect-error`

---

## INVIOLABLE: Branch + PR — never push to main

```bash
# 1. branch
git checkout -b feat/description   # or fix/ refactor/ chore/ docs/

# 2. commit with conventional prefix
git commit -m "feat: add job board integration"

# 3. PR — CI must pass
```

**Before starting any work, verify the current branch still exists on the remote:**
```bash
git fetch origin
git branch -r | grep $(git branch --show-current)
```
If not found (PR was merged and branch deleted on GitHub), switch to main first:
```bash
git checkout main && git pull origin main
```
Never commit to a branch that no longer exists on the remote.

---

## Architecture overview

```
packages/ui        → @ajh/ui (shared React component library)
packages/shared    → IPC contracts and types (no React, no Node)
packages/core/ai/data/workers → main process only (banned in renderer)
apps/desktop/renderer         → React UI (IPC via service hooks only)
```

---

## Import rules

### Use @ajh/ui — not @/components/ui/*

```ts
// ❌ BANNED
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button';

// ✅
import { Button } from '@ajh/ui';
import type { ButtonProps } from '@ajh/ui';
```

`components/ui/` is a legacy compatibility layer. `UpdateBanner` is the only file
worth importing from there — everything else lives in `@ajh/ui`.

### Prefer React.ComponentProps over importing prop types

```ts
// ✅ Preferred
type Props = React.ComponentProps<typeof Button>;

// ✅ When you need to extend
import type { ButtonProps } from '@ajh/ui';
interface MyProps extends ButtonProps { extra: string; }

// ❌ Unnecessary
import type { ButtonProps } from '@ajh/ui';  // just use ComponentProps
```

### import type for all type-only imports

```ts
import type { MyType } from '@/lib/types';  // ✅
import { MyType } from '@/lib/types';       // ❌
```

### Import order (auto-fixed: `pnpm lint:fix`)

1. `node:` → 2. External → 3. `@ajh/*` → 4. `@/` → 5. Relative

---

## UI primitives

```tsx
// ❌ ESLint error
<button />, <select />, <textarea />

// ✅
import { Button, SelectDropdown, TextArea } from '@ajh/ui';
```

Allowed raw: `<input type="range|file|checkbox|radio|hidden">`.

All UI components: Button, Input, TextArea, SelectDropdown, ModalShell, ConfirmModal,
EmptyState, ErrorState, GlassCard, RowSkeleton, CardSkeleton, StreamingText, OptionTile,
SettingsSection — `@ajh/ui`. PageShell — `@/components/layout/PageShell`.

---

## IPC boundary

```ts
// ❌ ESLint error in features/, routes/, components/
window.api.jobs.list()

// ✅
import { useJobs } from '@/services';
```

---

## Design system

```tsx
className="text-[#c084fc]"         // ❌ → className="text-brand-soft"
transition={{ duration: 0.18 }}    // ❌ → transition={transition.normal}  (from '@/lib/motion')
```

---

## Package boundary (renderer)

```
✅  @ajh/ui   @ajh/shared   @ajh/prompts
❌  @ajh/core  @ajh/ai  @ajh/data  @ajh/workers  (main process only)
```

Features must not import each other's internal components.

---

## Data fetching

No `useState + useEffect` for remote data → React Query service hooks only.

---

## New IPC capability

1. `packages/shared/src/ipc/contracts.ts` — signature
2. `apps/desktop/src/main/ipc/router.ts` — implementation
3. `apps/desktop/src/preload/index.ts` — exposure
4. `apps/desktop/src/renderer/services/` — hook

---

## Commit conventions

`feat:` minor · `fix:` `perf:` patch · `BREAKING CHANGE` footer: major
`refactor:` `docs:` `chore:` `ci:` `test:` — no release
